article.description: — David Roddy scored 24 points as Colorado State extended its home winning streak to eight games, edging past Utah State 77-72 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Roddy carries Colorado St. over Utah St. 77-72
article.linkText: Roddy carries Colorado St. over Utah St. 77-72
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- — David Roddy scored 24 points as Colorado State extended its home winning streak to eight games, edging past Utah State 77-72 on Wednesday night. Isaiah Stevens added 22 points for the Rams. Jalen Lake had 11 points for Colorado State (12-1, 2-1 Mountain West Conference). Chandler Jacobs added 11 points and nine rebounds. Sean Bairstow scored a career-high 20 points for the Aggies (10-6, 1-2). Brandon Horvath added 15 points and seven rebounds. Justin Bean had 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
